content.text: Good. Now let me create the worktree for the new feature branch:

input.command:
REPO_ROOT="/Users/randlee/Documents/github/claude-history"
WORKTREE_BASE="/Users/randlee/Documents/github/claude-history-worktrees"
BRANCH="feature/phase10-html-quality"
BASE="develop"
WORKTREE_PATH="$WORKTREE_BASE/$BRANCH"

# Check if the worktree path already exists
if [ -d "$WORKTREE_PATH" ]; then
  echo "ERROR: Worktree path already exists: $WORKTREE_PATH"
  exit 1
fi

# Create the worktree with -b to create the branch
cd "$REPO_ROOT"
git worktree add -b "$BRANCH" "$WORKTREE_PATH" "$BASE"
echo "Worktree created successfully"
